Both molecular forms of An. gambiae s.s. occur in sympatry but the S form increases in frequency (up to 85%) at the end of the rainy season (October–November). Knock-down (kdr) mutation occurs in both forms but at different frequencies (>90% in the S form and at around 20% for the M form).
